description: Hifab Group AB engages in the provision of project management. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm and currently employs 295 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2008-10-07. The company provides project management and advisory services for development and optimization of the resources. The company offers its services mainly to the building and construction sector. As of December 31, 2011, it operated four direct subsidiaries: Hifab Finans AB, offering project management in building, construction and environmental projects in Sweden; Hifab International, responsible for assignments financed by international development banks and agencies; Hifab Invest AB, focusing on planning of projects in early stages; and LBK Projektledning AB. The company operates 16 offices. In October 2014, it acquired all shares in Kanenergi Sweden AB.
name: Hifab Group AB
